---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PromptDemo from '../components/PromptDemo.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="SLP + LLM Field Guide">
    <div class="hero-wrapper">
        <section class="hero">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <div class="hero-label">
                    <span class="pulse-dot"></span>
                    Actively maintained field guide
                </div>
                <h1>SLP + LLM<br/>Field Guide</h1>
                <p class="tagline">A free, open clinical knowledge resource for SLPs. The people writing goals, reports, and session notes deserve to shape how that work gets done.</p>
                <div class="hero-principle">"A good prompt isn't a tech skill. It's clinical reasoning made visible."</div>

                <div class="io-explainer">
                    <p>
                        <strong>Why "I/O"?</strong> In computing, <em>I/O</em> means <em>input/output</em>: how a system receives and sends information. In speech-language pathology, that's what we do every day: we study how people take in language and produce it. SLP/IO sits at that intersection, where clinical communication meets the tools that process it.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="ai-disclosure">
                    <p>
                        <strong>Yes, this site was built with AI.</strong> That's the point. This resource was developed with language models as writing partners, for organizing, drafting, and refining. Every claim, principle, and recommendation has been reviewed and shaped through clinical judgment. We're not hiding the process; we're demonstrating what responsible use looks like in practice.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="hero-cta">
                    <a class="btn-primary" href="/foundations/">Read the foundations</a>
                    <a href="/tasks/" class="link-arrow">Jump to tasks →</a>
                </div>

                <div class="hero-meta">
                    <span><i class="ph-duotone ph-stethoscope"></i> Built by a clinician</span>
                    <span><i class="ph-duotone ph-scales"></i> Aligned with ASHA ethics</span>
                    <span><i class="ph-duotone ph-waveform"></i> A Harmonic Systems project</span>
                    <span><i class="ph-duotone ph-arrows-clockwise"></i> Last updated April 2026</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>

    <div class="section-divider"><hr/></div>

    <!-- ── Quick Start ── -->
    <section>
        <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-label">New here?</div>
            <h2>Start <span class="accent">Here</span></h2>
            <p class="section-intro">This isn't about learning AI. It's about articulating what you already know (your clinical expertise) clearly enough that any tool can work with it.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="quickstart-steps">
            <a href="/foundations/phi-safety/" class="quickstart-step">
                <div class="quickstart-number">1</div>
                <div class="quickstart-content">
                    <h4>Protect Patient Data</h4>
                    <p>Learn what can and cannot go into an LLM. Use the PHI safety checker to build good habits from day one.</p>
                </div>
                <i class="ph ph-arrow-right quickstart-arrow"></i>
            </a>
            <a href="/foundations/prompt-patterns/" class="quickstart-step">
                <div class="quickstart-number">2</div>
                <div class="quickstart-content">
                    <h4>Learn the Prompt Patterns</h4>
                    <p>Six patterns that aren't really about AI. They're about operationalizing your clinical knowledge so it translates into better output.</p>
                </div>
                <i class="ph ph-arrow-right quickstart-arrow"></i>
            </a>
            <a href="/tasks/writing-goals/" class="quickstart-step">
                <div class="quickstart-number">3</div>
                <div class="quickstart-content">
                    <h4>Write Your First Goal</h4>
                    <p>Put it into practice. The specificity of the output depends entirely on the clinical knowledge you bring to it.</p>
                </div>
                <i class="ph ph-arrow-right quickstart-arrow"></i>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="section-divider"><hr/></div>

    <!-- ── Interactive Demo ── -->
    <PromptDemo />

    <div class="section-divider"><hr/></div>

    <!-- ── Explore the Guide ── -->
    <section>
        <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-label">Explore</div>
            <h2>Find What You <span class="accent">Need</span></h2>
            <p class="section-intro">Enter from any angle. The guide is organized around four questions: What do I need to know? What am I trying to do? Where do I work? Did I do it right?</p>
        </div>

        <!-- LEARN -->
        <div class="group-label"><i class="ph-duotone ph-book-open"></i> Learn</div>
        <div class="layer-grid">
            <a href="/foundations/" class="layer-card">
                <div class="layer-icon"><i class="ph-duotone ph-compass"></i></div>
                <h3>Foundations</h3>
                <p>Core principles, PHI safety, how LLMs work, prompt patterns, evidence base, ethical decision trees, and model comparison.</p>
                <span class="layer-count">8 guides</span>
            </a>

            <a href="/glossary/" class="layer-card">
                <div class="layer-icon" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent-amber), #e67e22);"><i class="ph-duotone ph-translate"></i></div>
                <h3>Glossary</h3>
                <p>Every term defined from both sides, clinical and technical. SLPs and developers finally speaking the same language.</p>
                <span class="layer-count">25 terms</span>
            </a>

            <a href="/research/" class="layer-card">
                <div class="layer-icon" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2c3e50, #34495e);"><i class="ph-duotone ph-article"></i></div>
                <h3>Research Digests</h3>
                <p>Structured summaries of peer-reviewed studies on AI in healthcare and clinical documentation, focusing on what the evidence actually says.</p>
                <span class="layer-count">6 studies</span>
            </a>
        </div>

        <!-- DO -->
        <div class="group-label"><i class="ph-duotone ph-hammer"></i> Do</div>
        <div class="layer-grid">
            <a href="/prompts/" class="layer-card">
                <div class="layer-icon" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent-green), #2ecc71);"><i class="ph-duotone ph-terminal-window"></i></div>
                <h3>Prompt Library</h3>
                <p>Each prompt is an inventory of what a competent clinician knows (assessment frameworks, legal requirements, clinical reasoning) made actionable.</p>
                <span class="layer-count">12 prompts</span>
            </a>

            <a href="/workflows/" class="layer-card">
                <div class="layer-icon"><i class="ph-duotone ph-flow-arrow"></i></div>
                <h3>Workflows</h3>
                <p>Multi-step guides with decision points where clinical judgment overrides the tool. Not just prompts, but sequences.</p>
                <span class="layer-count">6 workflows</span>
            </a>

            <a href="/tasks/" class="layer-card">
                <div class="layer-icon"><i class="ph-duotone ph-clipboard-text"></i></div>
                <h3>Tasks</h3>
                <p>Goal writing, documentation, communication, compliance, clinical reasoning, and material creation.</p>
                <span class="layer-count">6 tasks</span>
            </a>
        </div>

        <!-- ADAPT -->
        <div class="group-label"><i class="ph-duotone ph-sliders-horizontal"></i> Adapt</div>
        <div class="layer-grid">
            <a href="/settings/" class="layer-card">
                <div class="layer-icon"><i class="ph-duotone ph-buildings"></i></div>
                <h3>Settings</h3>
                <p>Schools, medical/acute, SNF/rehab, early intervention, private practice, and university supervision.</p>
                <span class="layer-count">6 settings</span>
            </a>

            <a href="/domains/" class="layer-card">
                <div class="layer-icon"><i class="ph-duotone ph-circles-four"></i></div>
                <h3>Domains</h3>
                <p>Articulation, language, fluency, voice, pragmatics, cognitive-linguistic, dysphagia, AAC, literacy, and hearing.</p>
                <span class="layer-count">10 domains</span>
            </a>

            <a href="/patterns/" class="layer-card">
                <div class="layer-icon" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #7b2d8e, #9b59b6);"><i class="ph-duotone ph-tree-structure"></i></div>
                <h3>Clinical Patterns</h3>
                <p>Map your clinical philosophy to LLM interaction strategies. Naturalistic, discrete trial, family-centered; each approach is different.</p>
                <span class="layer-count">6 patterns</span>
            </a>
        </div>

        <!-- VERIFY -->
        <div class="group-label"><i class="ph-duotone ph-check-square"></i> Verify</div>
        <div class="layer-grid">
            <a href="/antipatterns/" class="layer-card">
                <div class="layer-icon" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent-red), #e74c3c);"><i class="ph-duotone ph-warning"></i></div>
                <h3>Antipatterns</h3>
                <p>Before-and-after examples that reveal clinical gaps, not AI mistakes. If you can't spot what's wrong, that's the lesson.</p>
                <span class="layer-count">8 antipatterns</span>
            </a>

            <a href="/case-studies/" class="layer-card">
                <div class="layer-icon" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent-green), #27ae60);"><i class="ph-duotone ph-users-three"></i></div>
                <h3>Case Studies</h3>
                <p>De-identified clinical scenarios showing real SLP workflows with AI: what worked, what failed, and lessons learned.</p>
                <span class="layer-count">5 cases</span>
            </a>

            <a href="/policies/" class="layer-card">
                <div class="layer-icon" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #7b2d8e, #9b59b6);"><i class="ph-duotone ph-shield-check"></i></div>
                <h3>Policy Templates</h3>
                <p>Adaptable AI governance templates for schools, hospitals, private practices, and clinical education programs.</p>
                <span class="layer-count">4 templates</span>
            </a>

            <a href="/resources/" class="layer-card">
                <div class="layer-icon"><i class="ph-duotone ph-book-open-text"></i></div>
                <h3>Resources</h3>
                <p>Digital media literacy, full references, changelog, and supporting materials.</p>
                <span class="layer-count">3 resources</span>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="section-divider"><hr/></div>

    <!-- ── Origin ── -->
    <section class="section-alt">
        <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-label">Origin</div>
            <h2>Why This <span class="accent">Exists</span></h2>
            <p class="section-intro">SLPs spend more time on paperwork than almost any other clinical task. The people doing that work should have a say in how it evolves, and the tools to make it better should be free.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card-grid">
            <div class="origin-card">
                <i class="ph-duotone ph-puzzle-piece"></i>
                <h4>The Gap</h4>
                <p>Documentation eats clinical hours. New tools can help, but only if they're built on real clinical knowledge, not generic AI hype. Clinicians needed a resource made for them, by one of them.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="origin-card">
                <i class="ph-duotone ph-code"></i>
                <h4>The Background</h4>
                <p>This resource is built by David Nyman, MS CCC-SLP, a school-based speech-language pathologist in New York who also writes software. That dual lens drives everything here.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="origin-card">
                <i class="ph-duotone ph-warning-circle"></i>
                <h4>The Problem</h4>
                <p>Paperwork is where clinical knowledge becomes a legal document. If new tools are going to touch that process, clinicians (not vendors) need to define the standards.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="origin-card">
                <i class="ph-duotone ph-target"></i>
                <h4>The Position</h4>
                <p>SLP/IO isn't pro-AI or anti-AI. It's pro-clinician. This resource is free because the knowledge it organizes already belongs to the profession. We're just making it easier to use.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="origin-statement">
            <strong>Harmonic Systems</strong> is the studio behind SLP/IO, a small operation where clinical practice and software development overlap. SLP/IO is its first public resource: a living document where the rigor of speech-language pathology meets the capability of modern language models.
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="section-divider"><hr/></div>

    <!-- ── About ── -->
    <section id="about">
        <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-label">Background</div>
            <h2>About <span class="accent">This Resource</span></h2>
        </div>
        <div class="about-text">
            <p>SLP/IO is a <strong>Harmonic Systems</strong> project, built by a speech-language pathologist and software developer who has spent years writing the same IEP goals, progress notes, and evaluation reports that you write.</p>
            <p>This resource is free because the knowledge inside it isn't new. It's what competent clinicians already know: assessment frameworks, legal standards, clinical reasoning, ethical boundaries. We just organized it in a way that makes it usable with modern tools. Clinicians deserve to participate in how their paperwork evolves, not have it decided for them.</p>
            <p>The question was never "should SLPs use AI?" It's "who defines what good looks like?" The answer should be clinicians. This is our attempt to make that happen.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="disclosure">
            <strong>About the author:</strong> David Nyman, MS CCC-SLP, is a school-based speech-language pathologist in the Hudson Valley region of New York. He splits his time between clinical work and building software tools informed by that practice. SLP/IO is his attempt to bridge the gap between what clinicians need and what the technology conversation currently offers.
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="section-divider"><hr/></div>

    <!-- ── Contact ── -->
    <section class="section-alt" id="contact">
        <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-label">Connect</div>
            <h2>Get <span class="accent">Involved</span></h2>
        </div>
        <div class="cta-section">
            <h3>Want to contribute, collaborate, or push back?</h3>
            <p>This guide gets better when clinicians challenge it. If you've found a use case we missed, a principle that needs nuance, or something that's flat-out wrong, that's exactly the kind of feedback that matters.</p>
            <a class="btn-primary" href="mailto:harmonicsystems.io@gmail.com">Send feedback</a>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    /* ── Hero ── */
    .hero-wrapper {
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--light) 0%, var(--primary-light) 50%, var(--secondary) 100%);
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
    }

    .hero-wrapper::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        top: -30%;
        right: -10%;
        width: 600px;
        height: 600px;
        background: radial-gradient(circle, var(--primary-glow) 0%, transparent 60%);
        pointer-events: none;
        animation: float 8s ease-in-out infinite;
    }

    .hero-wrapper::after {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        bottom: -20%;
        left: -10%;
        width: 450px;
        height: 450px;
        background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(39,174,96,0.08) 0%, transparent 60%);
        pointer-events: none;
        animation: float 10s ease-in-out infinite reverse;
    }

    .hero {
        max-width: 960px;
        margin: auto;
        min-height: calc(90vh - var(--header-height));
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        padding: 4rem 2rem;
        position: relative;
    }

    .hero-cta {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 1.25rem;
        margin-top: 2rem;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    @keyframes float {
        0%, 100% { transform: translate(0, 0); }
        50% { transform: translate(20px, -20px); }
    }

    .hero-content { position: relative; z-index: 1; max-width: 720px; }

    .hero-label {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 8px;
        font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--primary);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 1.5px;
        margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    }

    .pulse-dot {
        width: 8px;
        height: 8px;
        background: var(--accent-green);
        border-radius: 50%;
        animation: pulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;
    }

    @keyframes pulse {
        0%, 100% { opacity: 1; box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 rgba(39,174,96,0.4); }
        50% { opacity: 0.8; box-shadow: 0 0 0 8px rgba(39,174,96,0); }
    }

    .tagline {
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
    }

    .hero-principle {
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
        background: var(--primary-light);
        border-left: 4px solid var(--primary);
        border-radius: 0 var(--radius-sm) var(--radius-sm) 0;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--dark);
    }

    .io-explainer {
        margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
        padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: var(--radius);
        background: var(--light);
    }

    .io-explainer p {
        font-size: 0.88rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        margin: 0;
    }

    .io-explainer strong { color: var(--dark); }

    .ai-disclosure {
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
        border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-amber);
        border-radius: 0 var(--radius-sm) var(--radius-sm) 0;
        background: rgba(212,120,46,0.06);
    }

    .ai-disclosure p {
        font-size: 0.82rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        margin: 0;
    }

    .ai-disclosure strong { color: var(--dark); }

    .link-arrow {
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 0.88rem;
        color: var(--primary);
        text-decoration: none;
        border-bottom: 2px solid var(--primary);
        padding-bottom: 2px;
    }

    .hero-meta {
        display: flex;
        gap: 1.5rem;
        font-size: 0.78rem;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
        margin-top: 2rem;
    }

    .hero-meta span { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; }
    .hero-meta i { color: var(--primary); }

    /* ── Group Labels ── */
    .group-label {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 8px;
        font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 1.5px;
        color: var(--primary);
        margin-top: 2.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
        padding-left: 2px;
    }

    .group-label i { font-size: 1rem; }

    /* ── Layer Navigation Grid ── */
    .layer-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
        gap: 1.25rem;
        margin-top: 2rem;
    }

    .layer-card {
        padding: 1.75rem;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: var(--radius-organic);
        transition: all var(--transition);
        box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
        text-decoration: none;
        color: inherit;
        display: block;
        position: relative;
    }

    .layer-card:nth-child(even) { border-radius: 4px 10px 4px 10px; }

    .layer-card:hover {
        border-color: var(--primary);
        box-shadow: var(--card-shadow-hover);
        transform: translateY(-4px);
        color: inherit;
    }

    .layer-icon {
        width: 44px;
        height: 44px;
        border-radius: 10px;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        font-size: 1.35rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        color: var(--light);
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary), #3498db);
    }

    .layer-card h3 { font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
    .layer-card p { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }

    .layer-count {
        font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
        font-size: 0.65rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 1px;
        color: var(--primary);
    }

    /* ── Origin Cards ── */
    .origin-card {
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: var(--radius-organic);
        transition: all var(--transition);
        box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
    }

    .origin-card:nth-child(even) { border-radius: 4px 10px 4px 10px; }

    .origin-card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-3px);
        box-shadow: var(--card-shadow-hover);
    }

    .origin-card i { font-size: 1.3rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; display: block; }
    .origin-card h4 { font-size: 0.92rem; margin-bottom: 0.35rem; }
    .origin-card p { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.6; }

    .origin-statement {
        margin-top: 2rem;
        padding: 1.75rem;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary-light) 0%, rgba(52,152,219,0.05) 100%);
        border-radius: var(--radius);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-left: 4px solid var(--primary);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        color: var(--text-muted);
    }

    .origin-statement strong { color: var(--dark); }

    /* ── About ── */
    .about-text { font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.85; color: var(--text-muted); }
    .about-text p { margin-bottom: 1rem; }

    .disclosure {
        background: var(--secondary);
        border-radius: var(--radius);
        padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
        font-size: 0.82rem;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        line-height: 1.7;
        border-left: 4px solid var(--text-muted);
    }

    /* ── CTA ── */
    .cta-section {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 3.5rem 2rem;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary-light) 0%, rgba(39,174,96,0.05) 100%);
        border-radius: var(--radius);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    .cta-section h3 { font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
    .cta-section p { color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif; font-size: 0.9rem; }

    /* ── Quick Start ── */
    .quickstart-steps {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 1rem;
        margin-top: 2rem;
    }

    .quickstart-step {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 1.25rem;
        padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: var(--radius);
        text-decoration: none;
        color: inherit;
        transition: all var(--transition);
        box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
    }

    .quickstart-step:hover {
        border-color: var(--primary);
        box-shadow: var(--card-shadow-hover);
        transform: translateX(4px);
        color: inherit;
    }

    .quickstart-number {
        flex-shrink: 0;
        width: 44px;
        height: 44px;
        border-radius: 50%;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary), #3498db);
        color: white;
        font-family: 'Roboto Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
    }

    .quickstart-content { flex: 1; }
    .quickstart-content h4 { font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
    .quickstart-content p { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; }

    .quickstart-arrow {
        flex-shrink: 0;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        transition: all var(--transition);
    }

    .quickstart-step:hover .quickstart-arrow {
        color: var(--primary);
        transform: translateX(4px);
    }

    /* ── Mobile ── */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .hero {
            min-height: auto;
            padding: 2.5rem 1.25rem;
        }

        .hero-content { max-width: 100%; }

        h1 { font-size: 2rem; }

        .tagline {
